definition.value: A racemate comprising equimolar amounts of (R)- and (S)-sulconazole. An antifungal agent with activity against Candida species, it is used (generally as the nitrate salt) for the topical treatment of fungal skin infections.
An organic sodium salt that is the monosodium salt of sulfacetamide.
A sulfonamide consisting of pyrimidine with a 4-aminobenzenesulfonamido group at the 2-position.
